<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Install</summary>
  <p><strong>Part 1 — Remote Script (required)</strong></p>
  <ol>
    <li>Copy the entire <code>BeatDetective/</code> folder to Ableton's MIDI Remote Scripts directory:<br><code>/Applications/Ableton Live X.app/Contents/App-Resources/MIDI Remote Scripts/</code></li>
    <li>Restart Ableton Live</li>
    <li>Go to <strong>Preferences &rarr; Link / Tempo / MIDI &rarr; Control Surface</strong> and select <code>BeatDetective</code>. Leave MIDI input/output as None.</li>
  </ol>
  <p><strong>Part 2 — Max for Live UI (requires Suite)</strong></p>
  <ol>
    <li>Copy <code>BeatDetective.amxd</code> and <code>beat_detective_controller.js</code> to:<br><code>~/Music/Ableton/User Library/Presets/Audio Effects/Max Audio Effect/</code></li>
    <li>Drag <strong>BeatDetective</strong> from the browser onto any audio track</li>
  </ol>
</details>
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Features</summary>
  <ul class="tool-shortcuts">
    <li><strong>3 detection methods</strong> Warp markers, Live's transient API, or beat grid fallback</li>
    <li><strong>Configurable sensitivity</strong> Control how aggressively transients are detected (0&ndash;100%)</li>
    <li><strong>Quantize grid</strong> Snap slices to 1/4, 1/8, 1/16, or 1/32 grid</li>
    <li><strong>Auto-warp</strong> Warp clips before slicing for more accurate detection</li>
    <li><strong>Min slice length</strong> Prevent micro-slices by setting a minimum duration</li>
    <li><strong>Multi-clip support</strong> Select and process multiple clips at once</li>
    <li><strong>Headless mode</strong> Edit <code>settings.cfg</code> to control all parameters without Max for Live</li>
  </ul>
</details>
